The paper deals with stacked denoising autoencoders (SDAs) and their application to domain adaptation in natural language processing tasks such as sentiment analysis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
